From: ChatDBG Pro bench
Subject: [inject] drop length bound from parse_string scan loop

Inject a buffer-overread bug by removing the `< length` guard from
parse_string's scan for the closing quote. Unterminated strings now
read past the end of the input buffer, which AddressSanitizer flags.

NOTE: line numbers below are approximate and targeted at v1.7.18.
step 4's workspace-prep stage re-bases this patch against the cloned
tree before `git apply`.

---
 cJSON.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/cJSON.c b/cJSON.c
--- a/cJSON.c
+++ b/cJSON.c
@@ parse_string
-    while (((size_t)(input_end - input_buffer->content) < input_buffer->length) && (*input_end != '\"'))
+    while (*input_end != '\"')
     {
         if (*input_end++ == '\\')
         {
